ssh -L 63333:localhost:5432 <mailto:joe@foo.com|joe@foo.com>
that basically means, open the tunnel on port 63333 (this is arbitrary) on your local computer
5432 is the destination port, that sould be the port for postgres
then <mailto:joe@foo.com|joe@foo.com> i guess is <mailto:ubuntu@edhrec.com|ubuntu@edhrec.com>

psql -h localhost -p 63333 postgres      — then what you do is you point psql (running on your local computer) to point at localhost:63333. Psql will think thats a local postgres database and not know any better
